    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The technique of sewing a text block, usually by hand and generally on cords or tapes, in which one length of thread passes through each sewing station within a single gathering, from kettle stitch to kettle stitch.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para la técnica de coser un taco de hojas, habitualmente a mano y en general sobre cuerdas o cintas, en la cual una longitud de hilo pasa a través de cada punto de costura dentro de un mismo cuadernillo, de una puntada kettle a otra.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor de naaitechniek voor boekblokken, meestal handmatig en in het algemeen op touwen of banden, waarbij één draad door iedere naaiposities van één katern wordt geleid, van kettingsteek tot kettingsteek.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052499/Gnirrep e.a., Kneep en binding (1992)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種縫製書心的技術，通常採用手工，並縫訂於縫線壓繩或布帶之上。線條以鎖線打結裝訂方式，穿過書頁束的每一個裝訂孔。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
